707537f-b.title: Manhattan: 1st Ave. - 23rd St. E.
707537f-b.text:
First Ave., east side, north from East 23rd Street (foreground,
not seen), showing in the background tne Bellevue Hospital building
outline. In the foreground, at the N.E. corner of East 23rd Street,
appears a portion of the Institute for Crippled and Disabled. Occupying
the S.E. corner of East 24th Street is a gasoline station. No. 2, of
this set shows the last mentioned features in detail.
May 8, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.

707538f-a.title: Manhattan: 1st Ave. - 23rd St.
707538f-a.text:
First Avenue,West Side,23rd to 24th Streets,across excavation.
August 31,1930.
P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

707532f-a.title: Manhattan: 1st Ave. - 23rd St. E.
707532f-a.text:
First Ave., east side, south from and including East 23rd Street.
The Second Ave. Elevated is included.
May 23, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

707540f-a.title: Manhattan: 1st Ave. - 23rd St. E.
707540f-a.text:
First Ave., east side, north from, but not including East 23rd., to,
but not including 26th Strcets.
May 23, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

707539f-a.title: Manhattan: 1st Ave. - 23rd St.
707539f-a.text:
First Ave., west side, south from East 24th., to 23rd Streets. Gas
station in the foreground, is on the S.E. corner of East 24th Street.
May 25, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

707533f-a.title: Manhattan: 1st Ave. - 23rd St.
707533f-a.text:
First Avenue, east side, south from E. 23rd Street. The
2nd Avenue "gg" line veers on 23rd Street to connect with its
designated thoroughfare. On the left is a gas station at the
S. E. corner. This is of recent construction. Overhead are
gasholders of the Consolidated Edison Company.
View 1: Say 8, 1938
View 2: July 19, 1939
P. L. Sperr
